## Working Rules

- Use the venv at `.venv/`. Never install packages globally.
- Run tests with `pytest` before considering any change done.
- Keep `pyproject.toml` as the single source of truth for dependencies — no `requirements.txt`.
- Prefer small, composable functions/modules over large files.
- Type-hint everything; `mypy --strict` should stay clean.
- Don't `git commit` without being asked, unless the user has told you to commit at natural checkpoints.

## Debugging Log Protocol

If you get stuck in a debugging loop (multiple failed attempts at the same problem) and eventually resolve it, append an entry to `rules/` describing:
- What the symptom was
- What approaches failed and why
- What actually fixed it

Keep entries short and factual. This is a project-local memory so future sessions don't repeat the same dead ends. See root `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` for the full protocol.
